     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d137n2-ptr" id="PJA05d137n2">2</a>
      <p>The expedition against the British in Rhode Island. See <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to James Bowdoin, 16 April, notes <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-05-02-0088&amp;expandNote=PJA05d091n2#PJA05d091n2" class="document">2</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-05-02-0088&amp;expandNote=PJA05d091n3#PJA05d091n3" class="document">3</a> (above).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d137n3-ptr" id="PJA05d137n3">3</a>
      <p>That is, lack.</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d137n4-ptr" id="PJA05d137n4">4</a>
      <p>On the act regulating prices, see William Tudor to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 16 March, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-05-02-0061&amp;expandNote=PJA05d064n4#PJA05d064n4" class="document">note 4</a> (above). The House considered the repeal on 10 June (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the House of Representatives of Massachusetts&lt;/i&gt; [[1715-]], Boston, reprinted by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 1919-. (For the years for which reprints are not yet available, the original printings are cited, by year and session.) ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">House Jour.</span></span>, 17771778, 1st sess., p. 19, 20).</p>
     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA05d137n5-ptr" id="PJA05d137n5">5</a>
